Map 1 -- * Feature
A Feature has A Map. It must always have exactly, one, and can never have none. And there is an upper bound of at most one Map.
A Map has some Features. It can have none, and there is no upper bound defined.
When a Feature is created, its Map must be assigned. When a Feature is deleted, its Map is not deleted and its list of Features is decreased. When a Map is deleted, its Features are not deleted. They are assigned to another Map.
